{"at": "2026-06-01T15:56:34.083399+00:00", "event_id": "01KT1YDBX3WRFFQK2XGCE20WJY", "event_type": "DecisionPointResolved", "payload": {"actual_participants": [], "closed_locally_while_widened": false, "closure_message": null, "decision_point_id": "01KT1Y3V0KBN7PA24P7E28AH32", "final_answer": "Single mission to preserve shared functional context. Decompose into many small WPs (granular preferred over large chunks); sequence by dependency: integrity/diagnostics first, then DRG relationship authority + merge relocation, then DRG-fragment authoring migration, then activation/cascade, OperationalContext, and #1333 templates.", "mission_id": "01KT1TV1KPRFH00FMPBM4JWGHZ", "mission_slug": "org-doctrine-profile-integrity-activation-closure-01KT1TV1", "mission_type": "software-dev", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "other_answer": false, "rationale": null, "recorded_at": "2026-06-01T15:56:34.083399Z", "resolved_by": "cli", "run_id": "01KT1Y3V0KBN7PA24P7E28AH32", "state_entered_at": "2026-06-01T15:56:34.082850Z", "summary": null, "terminal_outcome": "resolved"}}
{"at": "2026-06-01T15:56:43.053864+00:00", "event_id": "01KT1YDMND3660RAN1XKWDAQFA", "event_type": "DecisionPointOpened", "payload": {"actor_id": "cli", "actor_type": "human", "decision_point_id": "01KT1YDMND3660RAN1XKWDAQF9", "input_key": "field_retirement_strategy", "mission_id": "01KT1TV1KPRFH00FMPBM4JWGHZ", "mission_slug": "org-doctrine-profile-integrity-activation-closure-01KT1TV1", "mission_type": "software-dev", "options": ["Deprecation window: tolerate fields (read+warn, auto-project to DRG), remove later", "Hard cutover: migrate all artifacts to DRG fragments in this mission, fields rejected", "Tolerate built-in fields indefinitely as projection, only org/project packs must use fragments"], "origin_flow": "plan", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "phase": "PLAN", "question": "OQ-2 chose DRG-fragment-only authoring, retiring the enhances/overrides/specializes_from FIELDS. How should existing field-authored artifacts (built-in doctrine + the 5 kinds #1291 just shipped + agent profiles) transition?", "recorded_at": "2026-06-01T15:56:43.053864Z", "run_id": "01KT1YDMND3660RAN1XKWDAQF9", "state_entered_at": "2026-06-01T15:56:43.053331Z", "step_id": "plan.migration.field-retirement"}}
{"at": "2026-06-01T15:59:02.498963+00:00", "event_id": "01KT1YHWV2011ZKS4MVQNFN09P", "event_type": "DecisionPointResolved", "payload": {"actual_participants": [], "closed_locally_while_widened": false, "closure_message": null, "decision_point_id": "01KT1YDMND3660RAN1XKWDAQF9", "final_answer": "Hard cutover. 3.2.0 is unreleased, so rc/bleeding-edge breakage is acceptable and preferred over a deprecation window that would leave problematic dual-path code. Migrate all built-in + shipped artifacts (incl. the 5 #1291 kinds and agent_profile.specializes_from) to DRG-fragment authoring in this mission; the relationship FIELDS become a validation error. No tolerate/auto-project compatibility path.", "mission_id": "01KT1TV1KPRFH00FMPBM4JWGHZ", "mission_slug": "org-doctrine-profile-integrity-activation-closure-01KT1TV1", "mission_type": "software-dev", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "other_answer": false, "rationale": null, "recorded_at": "2026-06-01T15:59:02.498963Z", "resolved_by": "cli", "run_id": "01KT1YDMND3660RAN1XKWDAQF9", "state_entered_at": "2026-06-01T15:59:02.498396Z", "summary": null, "terminal_outcome": "resolved"}}
{"at": "2026-06-01T15:59:11.571271+00:00", "event_id": "01KT1YJ5PKGHJTNXPKP0EG58QV", "event_type": "DecisionPointOpened", "payload": {"actor_id": "cli", "actor_type": "human", "decision_point_id": "01KT1YJ5PJ8MV48KZF53XEE3NV", "input_key": "template_identity", "mission_id": "01KT1TV1KPRFH00FMPBM4JWGHZ", "mission_slug": "org-doctrine-profile-integrity-activation-closure-01KT1TV1", "mission_type": "software-dev", "options": ["Mission-qualified name as ID (e.g. software-dev/spec) minted as DRG template nodes", "Add explicit id field/frontmatter to template files, mint DRG nodes from it", "Discovery+listing only; do NOT make templates DRG nodes (keep name-based resolution)"], "origin_flow": "plan", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "phase": "PLAN", "question": "#1333: templates today are resolved by name/path through 5 tiers, have no ID and no file extension, and live in mission-scoped dirs. To make them DRG-addressable (template:<id>) and listable per C-009, what identity scheme should templates use?", "recorded_at": "2026-06-01T15:59:11.571271Z", "run_id": "01KT1YJ5PJ8MV48KZF53XEE3NV", "state_entered_at": "2026-06-01T15:59:11.570711Z", "step_id": "plan.templates.identity"}}
{"at": "2026-06-01T16:00:24.139679+00:00", "event_id": "01KT1YMCJBZB76XAAWMHH2BN6Z", "event_type": "DecisionPointResolved", "payload": {"actual_participants": [], "closed_locally_while_widened": false, "closure_message": null, "decision_point_id": "01KT1YJ5PJ8MV48KZF53XEE3NV", "final_answer": "Mission-qualified name as template ID (e.g. software-dev/spec). Mint DRG template nodes from the existing tier+mission+filename layout \u2014 no template-file frontmatter churn. Disambiguates same-named templates across missions; templates become DRG-addressable (template:<id>) per C-009.", "mission_id": "01KT1TV1KPRFH00FMPBM4JWGHZ", "mission_slug": "org-doctrine-profile-integrity-activation-closure-01KT1TV1", "mission_type": "software-dev", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "other_answer": false, "rationale": null, "recorded_at": "2026-06-01T16:00:24.139679Z", "resolved_by": "cli", "run_id": "01KT1YJ5PJ8MV48KZF53XEE3NV", "state_entered_at": "2026-06-01T16:00:24.139069Z", "summary": null, "terminal_outcome": "resolved"}}
